Commentary: A loud shout for LBW but turned down! Tim Southee has a word with the keeper and the bowler and takes the review. It did look close in real-time but the on-field umpire thought otherwise. Pitched up by Kyle Jamieson, on middle, Zakir Hasan looks to work it across the line but his head is in no position as it falls over and the ball jags back in to ping him on the front pad. There is a spike on UltraEdge as the ball is next to the bat and therefore, the on-field decision will stand. New Zealand lose an early review.

Commentary: OUT! LBW! That is a huge wicket down for New Zealand as it is their master batter Kane Williamson walks off for just 11 runs in this innings and it is once again Taijul Islam who gets his man for the second time in this Test match. Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT! That is the end of the New Zealand innings. Taijul Islam claims his 10th wicket in the match as he picks up his 6th of this innings to get rid of Ish Sodhi. Ish Sodhi on the front foot looking to adjust to the bounce but could only loop it up for Zakir Hasan standing at silly point who takes a comfortable catch to end this New Zealand innings. Its Bangladesh who beat New Zealand for the first time in Bangladesh in a Test match.
Default_Commentary: 71.1: Taijul Islam to Ish Sodhi, OUT! c Zakir Hasan b Taijul Islam.
